post_text:
Dear Members of the Pennoyer School District Community,

After many years of dedicated and distinguished service, Board Members John Kovalcik and Gino Nardulli have decided to retire from the Board of Education.

As a result, we now have two vacancies on the Board that can be filled by "appointment" of the Board. If you are interested in being considered for a seat on the Pennoyer School District #79 Board of Education, please contact Wendy in the office for a packet of information. The Board asks for a letter of intent as well as a resume. The Board will conduct interviews of prospective candidates, with final decisions planned for the end of May, 2013.

For more information on Board Service, please visit the website of the Illinois Association of School Boards, http://www.iasb.com

Michael Lubelfeld Ed.D.
Superintendent

Pennoyer School District #79
5200 North Cumberland Avenue
Norridge, IL 60706

(708) 456-9094, fax: (708) 456-9098
